## Критерии остановки: аналитическая достаточность (Stopping criteria: analytic sufficiency), Guide 0.4.3

Stop only when all three “legs” are satisfied:

### A) Data completeness

- Entire material analyzed
- Key anomalies/lacunae addressed or explicitly documented as unresolved-but-significant
- Theoretical saturation: new cycles add little new, no meaningful model change

### B) Model coherence

- Internal non-contradiction
- Explains maximal facts with minimal ad hoc assumptions
- Central hypotheses survived targeted falsification; alternatives considered and rejected with reasons

### C) Pragmatic value

- Explains morphogenesis / etiology / ontogenesis at adequate depth
- Produces testable forecasts (with risk qualification)
- Answers the original diagnostic question (scope-fit)

